<comment type="function">
<text evidence="1">Catalyzes the attachment of serine to tRNA(Ser). Is also able to aminoacylate tRNA(Sec) with serine, to form the misacylated tRNA L-seryl-tRNA(Sec), which will be further converted into selenocysteinyl-tRNA(Sec) (By similarity).</text>
</comment>
<comment type="catalytic activity">
<text>ATP + L-serine + tRNA(Ser) = AMP + diphosphate + L-seryl-tRNA(Ser).</text>
</comment>
<comment type="catalytic activity">
<text>ATP + L-serine + tRNA(Sec) = AMP + diphosphate + L-seryl-tRNA(Sec).</text>
</comment>
<comment type="pathway">
<text>Aminoacyl-tRNA biosynthesis; selenocysteinyl-tRNA(Sec) biosynthesis; L-seryl-tRNA(Sec) from L-serine and tRNA(Sec): step 1/1.</text>
</comment>
